I bought food from this place 3 times and the food was ok. I had a bad experience on the 4th visit. When I first walked in, there was a faint rotten smell of meat lingering in the lobby. I ignored it and proceeded to order fried chicken wings and white rice, which is my usual order. When I got home, I dug in because I was very hungry. The white rice was the same as always but the chicken nearly made me puke. I'm 52 years old so I know bad sh#t when I taste it. The chicken had a rancid, rotten taste to it. It was too bad to eat because if I had tried, I would have gotten sick. The chicken had obviously gone beyond it's fresh date and they attempted to season and cook it hoping I wouldn't detect rotten chicken after it was fried. I'm very disappointed that they tried to cut corners instead of throwing bad sh#t away. I will never order from here again.
